Our website collects names, email addresses, and other personal information from customers and visitors through some of our online forms, including our subscription form and newsletter registration form. If you are a print subscriber we may, from time to time, exchange or rent your print subscription information with reputable companies that offer valuable marketing or products to our print subscribers. If you prefer that we do not share this information, you may opt-out at any time by contacting customer service at (800) 627-9533.</p><p dir="ltr">Customers can edit their personal information by logging into the secured area of our site.<br/><br/>
Our website contains links to other websites. Please note that when you click on one of these links, you are entering another website, for which americamagazine.org is not responsible.<br/><br/>
Our website utilizes services from third parties that may use cookies, web beacons and similar technologies to collect or receive information from our website and elsewhere on the internet and use that information to provide measurement services and target ads. Users can opt out of the collection and use of information for ad targeting by <a href="http://optout.aboutads.info">following the instructions here.</a><br/><br/>
If you wish to be removed from our email list, you can simply click on the “unsubscribe” link at the bottom of our emails.<br/><br/>
By using americamagazine.org, you signify your agreement to our privacy policy as stated above. Note that this policy may be revised periodically without notice. Please re-read this policy prior to submitting any personal information if you have concerns about how your information is being collected and used.</p><h4>Terms and Conditions for Social Login Services</h4><p>If you opt to log in to this website using a connected social service such as Twitter, Facebook or Google, we will, with your authorization, obtain your name and email address from that service and establish an account. We will use any information obtained under the same conditions as described above. We will not gather email addresses or contact information of any of your social media connections, friends or contacts, nor initiate any postings on your behalf, without your explicit authorization of any of those actions.</p><p> </p><p> </p></div><span class="a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 addtoany_list" data-a2a-url="http://www.americamagazine.org/privacy-policy" data-a2a-title="Privacy Policy"><div class="soucialLinks"><a href="" title="facebook" class="a2a_button_facebook facebook"></a></div><div class="soucialLinks"><a href="" title="twitter" class="a2a_button_twitter twitter"></a></div><div class="soucialLinks"><a href="" title="mail" class="a2a_button_email mail"></a></div><div class="soucialLinks"><a href="" title="print" class="a2a_button_printfriendly print"></a></div></span></div></article></div></div></div></div><div class="container"><div class="row"></div></div><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12 "><div class="region region-full-content-3"><section id="block-dfptagarticleleaderboardbtf728x90970x90" class="all-page-articles-leaderboard-btf block block-dfp block-dfp-adb57ade60-602f-430b-a973-80109a429464 clearfix"><div id="js-dfp-tag-article_leaderboard_btf_728x90_970x90"><script type="text/javascript">
